<HEADLINE> Nigeria Committed to One China Policy: Senate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Senate President Evans
Enwerem Thursday reaffirmed Nigeria's commitment to One China
policy.
</P>
<P>
Receiving Chinese Ambassador to Nigeria Liang Yinzhu here, he
praised China for its position in the U.N. Security Council for
the benefit of the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Enwerem noted that China's position has given meaning to the
"concept of South-South cooperation", and commended China's
contribution to the development of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"Since bilateral relations were established in 1971, both
countries have enjoyed warm relations as could be seen in their
cooperation in various fields," he told the Chinese ambassador.
</P>
<P>
In his remarks, Liang spoke highly of Nigeria's support for the
peaceful reunification of China with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He repeated a request made to the speaker of the House of
Representatives for the exchange of visits between the legislators
of both countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
