<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Strengthens Ties with Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and Cuba Thursday
reached an understanding on setting up a joint commission and Cuba
suggested that the first meeting of the commission be held in
Havana, the Ethiopia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The understanding was reached here when Ethiopian Prime
Minister Meles Zenawi held discussions with visiting Cuban
Deputy-Minister of Foreign Affairs Angel Dalmau Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Meles was quoted by the report as saying that Ethiopia desires
to further strengthen its relation with Cuba.
</P>
<P>
During the discussions, Fernandez said Cuba is preparing to
bolster its cooperation with Ethiopia particularly in the areas of
education, health and trade.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban deputy foreign minister arrived here Wednesday for a
four-day visit to Ethiopia. He also held talks Thursday with
Ethiopian Foreign Minister Seyoum Mesfin and other senior
government officials.
</P>
<P>
An economic cooperation agreement will be signed between the
two countries in the near future, said the Ethiopian Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and Ethiopia established diplomatic relations in 1976.
Cuba provided support to Ethiopia in education, health and defense
in the late 1970's and 80's. About 4,000 Ethiopians have attended
schools in Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
