<HEADLINE> Flights Canceled in Greece As Olympic Employees Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- More than half of Greece's Olympic
Airways (OA) flights were canceled on Thursday as a result of the
24-hour strike held by its employees who are protesting the
handover of the airline's management to Speedwing, a British
Airways subsidiary, for the next 30 months.
</P>
<P>
Forty-six out of 77 domestic and international flights, as well
as 27 out of 45 Olympic Aviation flights, have been canceled on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The airline's unionists warned that they would stage more
strikes through the season.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government has sunk billions of drachmas into the
ill- fated restructuring programs and repeatedly covered debts at
the national carrier.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the government decided that Speedwing would take
over the management of the airline in order to make it more
competitive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
