<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP Must Reinvent Way of Doing Business in Coping With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The new administrator for
the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), Mark Malloch Brown,
begins his four-year term Thursday, vowing to address
unprecedented global challenges and be reinvent its way of doing
business.
</P>
<P>
Brown told a press conference that the momentum of a declining
resource base for UNDP has not been broken, and that indeed, it is
accelerating.
</P>
<P>
Two UNDP donors have just indicated major cuts, one to finance
relief in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, the other to conform to
the Masstricht balanced budget in Europe, he said.
</P>
<P>
Asserting that this was a moment of truth for UNDP and its
Executive Board, Brown said that the organization would "attack
its business strategy for the next nine months with a passionate
sense of urgency."
</P>
<P>
He pledged that, by next spring, UNDP would "define its driving
goals and benchmarks, concentrate its business vision, set up
efficiency, accelerate its results-oriented and strengthen its
management team."
</P>
<P>
Brown comes to UNDP at a time when the world faces a
development crisis, when shrinking aid resources are challenging
UNDP's capacity to remain relevant.
</P>
<P>
"UNPD's funding crisis is part of the wider crisis in ODA (the
Official Development Assistance)," he said. "That wider crisis
amounts to a failure of imagination that threatens to sap the
international community's response in a time when more, not less,
development cooperation is needed."
</P>
<P>
"Ours is a generation with unprecedented possibilities for
human betterment. yet the mismatch between those possibilities and
our priorities is mind-boggling, as last year's Human Development
Report exposed," he said, "With just 9 billion U.S. dollars a
year, the world could deliver safe water and sanitation to all,
ending the transmission of debilitating water-borne diseases."
</P>
<P>
"With only 6 billion U.S. dollars more in annual spending, we
could give a basic education to every child on earth," he said.
</P>
<P>
But despite the fund challenges facing UNDP and the
international aid community, Brown said that this is a great time
to be in development because of advances in such areas as
information technologies, global communications and opportunities
presented by globalization and new drugs and vaccines.
</P>
<P>
UNDP is entering a new millennium with a strong strategic
advantage as a development cooperation organization that is rooted
in its "universality" represented by its presence in 133 program
countries, its many years of development cooperation with those
countries and its role as the coordination arm of the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
"These unique attributes allow UNDP an important role in
helping countries respond to the challenges of change in the new
millennium. Such challenges include choices to improve governance
and national capacity, strategies for post-conflict
rehabilitation, and urgent management decisions concerning
international trade, energy, the environment and social and
economic program," he said.
</P>
<P>
Brown, a former vice-president of external affairs of the World
Bank, was nominated for UNDP chief by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan and confirmed by the General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He succeeds James Gustave Speth, who held the post for six
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
