<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Universiada Flame to Arrive at Palma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA DE MALLORCA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- An Italian warship is to
escort the flame of the University Games from Torino of Italy to
Palma de Mallorca, Spain, where the 20th edition of the event will
be staged from July 3rd to 13th.
</P>
<P>
The relay of the flame will take place upon its arrival. The
relay runner Gabriel Vidal, a well-known Majorca player who took
the Barcelona Olympics soccer gold with his Spanish peers, will
light the first torch.
</P>
<P>
The bearers' relay will be every 300 meters, passing the fire
from one to another among the 152 relay runners who will cover the
trajectory of the university fire.
</P>
<P>
The third and last day of the relay will be closed out by
Miquel Angel Nadal, another Majorca-born footballer who now plays
with the prestigious Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
The torch will be kept aflame until July 13th, the final day of
the Universiada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
