<HEADLINE> Thailand Raises Export Target of Electronic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government has set a new
target for exports of electronic products at one trillion baht (27
billion U.S. dollars) annually, or one percent of the world's
trade on the products, Thai Industry Minister Suwat Liptapallop
said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet had ordered the Industry Ministry to seek ways
to boost exports of the electronic and electrical products, sugar
and sugar canes, Suwat was quoted by Thai News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's current level of exports of electronic products
stands at 400 billion baht (10.8 billion dollars), or 0.5 percent
of the global trade of the goods.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has also set a target of four percent growth in
exports for the year 1999 to 56 billion U.S. dollars. However, the
central bank has lowered the projection to 2.1 percent due to the
unsatisfactory performance of the sector in the first five months
of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
