</P>
<P>
"Germany is not going to just show up and hang out and try to
give us a game," Hamm says.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. team practiced penalty kicks yesterday. If the game
istied after 90 minutes of regulation adn 30 minutes of sudden-
deathovertime, the Americans are prepared to win the game on
penalty kicks.
</P>
<P>
"I have told them if you're going to prepare to take penalty
kicks, then prepare to make penalty kicks," coach Tony DiCicco
says.)
</P>
<P>
After a run of comfortable wins by the USA, a close game is
expected when two of the top four seeds meet. "We'd be very happy
with a 2-1 win," assistant coach Lauren Gregg says.
</P>
<P>
"The Germans are the best in combination play in the world,"
says DiCicco. "They can knock circles around you." 
