<HEADLINE> Bangkok to Host Regional Forum on Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government and the United
Nations High Commissioner on Human Rights will jointly organize a
workshop on human rights for countries and regions in Asia and the
Pacific here next week, the Thai News Agency said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Thai Foreign Ministry spokesman Don Pramudiwinai was quoted as
saying that the three-day workshop, starting from July 5, was
aimed at drafting national plans on promotion and protection of
human rights.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of 34 countries and regions in the
Asia-Pacific, as well as those from national institutions on human
rights, U.N. agencies, international organizations, private
bodies, and foreign diplomats in Thailand would take part in the
workshop, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the forum would include exchanges of views and
opinions, he said.
</P>
<P>
