<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Underlines Science, Technology for National Defense Industry (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji today
urged people working in science and technology related to national
defense to make new contributions to the development of that
industry and the nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
Zhu addressed a ceremony for the founding of 10 military-
industrial groups today, where he said that the military-
industrial corporations being restructured into the new groups is
an important step in reforming management structures of the
science and technology industry in national defense, improving
competitiveness of related enterprises, and accelerating national
defense modernization.
</P>
<P>
He said that the science and technology for national defense is
a key strategic industry and an important material and
technological basis of national defense modernization and that the
industry's strength is a reflection of national strength.
</P>
<P>
He said that the newly-established groups should make an effort
in 5 areas: separating government from businesses; setting up a
mechanism of fair competition; concentrating scientific research
on ensuring production and development of weaponry and equipment;
promoting better military-industrial layout and restructuring; and
creating a good environment for enterprises to free themselves
from difficulties and get reinvigorated.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0043 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Underlines Science, Technology for National Defense Industry (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said the groups should be shaped into economic entities that
are solely responsible for their own profits and losses and urged
that they play by the rules of the market.
</P>
<P>
The Commission of Science and Technology for National Defense
Industry should play a role in supervising the industry and
drawing up policies, laws, regulations, and standards governing
the development of these groups, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The premier stressed that earnest efforts be made to speed up
the development of China's weaponry and equipment to meet the
growing demand of its military forces.
</P>
<P>
Measures should also be taken to adjust the structures in the
science and technology industry related to national defense, he
noted, adding that more advanced technology should be introduced
to boost the industry.
</P>
<P>
He urged the industry to develop products and technology for
both military and civilian purposes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Underlines Science, Technology for National Defense Industry (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that the development of the industry depends
not only on hard work by those in the sector but also on support
from all segments of society. He asked related departments under
the State Council and governments at all levels to be fully aware
of the importance of the industry and help solve problems arising
in the course of reforming, adjusting and developing the industry.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo read a congratulatory letter from
President Jiang Zemin for the ceremony and unveiled the plaques of
the 10 groups at today's meeting.
</P>
