<HEADLINE> S. Africa Appoints Chairman of Arbitration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Vincent Mntambo has been
appointed as chairman of the governing body of the Commission for
Conciliation, Mediation and Arbitration ( CCMA), the CCMA
announced in Johannesburg Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The CCMA is a tripartite organization of representatives of
government, organized labor and business that resolves industrial
relations disputes. And the governing body oversees the strategy
and sets policy direction for the CCMA.
</P>
<P>
Since leaving government as the first director-general of the
Gauteng Province, Mntambo has focused on consulting and advising
top managers in both the private and public sector in the areas of
strategy and transformation, the CCMA said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Mntambo, who is one of the five founding partners of the Sediba
 Consulting, will serve as CCMA chairman for three years,
according to the statement. 
</P>
