<HEADLINE> UK Manufacturing Returns To Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON. July 1 (Xinhua) -- The UK manufacturing industry
expanded for the first time for more than a year in June as both
domestic and overseas orders increased, according to the latest
research.
</P>
<P>
The return to growth comes on the back of increasing orders and
higher factory output, the research by the Chartered Institute of
Purchasing and Supply (CIPS) found.
</P>
<P>
It's purchasing managers index was 50.4 in June, up from 49.4
in May and the first reading above 50 since March last year when
it was 51.1. A figure above 50 indicates expansion, below 50
contraction.
</P>
<P>
Roy Ayliffe, director of professional practice at CIPS, said:
"This is the best news the manufacturing economy has had for
fifteen months."
</P>
<P>
CIPS' separate index on total manufacturing output also grew
for the third month in a row, with the index showing 53 for June,
up from 52.4 in May.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the recent strengthening of order books, firms
continued to concentrate on cutting costs and improving
efficiencies wherever possible," the CIPS said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
