<HEADLINE> IMF Says Estonia Well Positioned for Economic Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Estonia's economy is well
positioned for a recovery, but further efforts are needed to
accelerate the implementation of the remaining structural reforms,
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After increasing by nearly 12 percent in 1997, Estonia's
economy slowed to 4 percent in 1998 and appears to have contracted
in early 1999, largely because of the situation in neighboring
countries and related banking system difficulties.
</P>
<P>
In an annual review of the Estonian economy, the IMF praised
the authorities for its success in narrowing current account
deficit, reducing inflation and implementing essential structural
reforms.
</P>
<P>
"Directors recognized that the immediate difficulties in the
banking system had now been successfully overcome, and considered
that Estonia's economy was well positioned for a recovery," the
IMF said.  
</P>
