<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Missing Myanmar Aircraft Crashes Near Sittway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A missing Myanmar aircraft of the
state-run Myanma Airways crashed on Friday afternoon near an
island in Sittway, the country's western Rakhine state, just a few
minutes before landing, the official Radio Myanmar reported.
</P>
<P>
The wreckage of the aircraft, Fokker XYAEO, was discovered in
the west of Phayonka island by an aircraft of the Myanmar Air
Force, it said.
</P>
<P>
The cargo aircraft, carrying construction materials on a
chartered flight from Yangon to Sittway, took off at the Yangon
International Airport Friday afternoon at about 1 p.m. (local
time).
</P>
<P>
When it approached Sittway and was 16 kilometers away from the
Sittway airport, the aircraft lost contact with the airport
control tower there at about 2:27 p.m. (local time) due to the bad
weather condition, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue work is underway, the report added, without disclosing
the casualties.
</P>
<P>
In January and August last year, two Myanmar passenger Fokker
aircraft crashed in Thandwe, the southwestern Rakhine state, and
Tachilek, the eastern Shan state, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
