<HEADLINE> Flood Battle On Yangtze River (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Over a million people in Jiangsu Province on the lower reaches
are fighting day and night to repair some 6,700 dangerous leaks in
dams as water levels reached a record high. So far, the province
has pumped the water from 60 percent of the planted fields that
were flooded and restored production at 354 flood-damaged plants.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Meteorology Station (CMS), the rain
finally stopped along the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze
early today after 10 days of heavy downpours.
</P>
<P>
Since June 22, heavy rains have fallen in provinces of Zhejiang,
Jiangsu, Anhui and Jiangxi, causing floods along some parts of the
Yangtze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
