<HEADLINE> Iran Expresses Concern Over Afghan Civil War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi has expressed concern over the incessant civil war in
Afghanistan, the Foreign Ministry said on Friday in a press
release.
</P>
<P>
"War of attrition and never-ending blood letting in
Afghanistan has proved that the crisis in Afghanistan has no
military solution and that neither a political faction nor an
ethnic group is capable of imposing its will over the rest of
Afghans," said Kharrazi.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed the recent invitation of United Nation
Secretary-General Kofi Annan to different Afghan factions and
ethnic groups to return to the negotiation table, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a report to the U.N. Security Council, Annan on Wednesday
urged the Afghan belligerent parties to resume direct talks
"unconditionally and without delay" to restore peace and stability
in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Annan called on countries concerned to improve coordination for
a common approach towards the settlement of Afghan crisis.
</P>
