<HEADLINE> Hot Weather Pushes Up Beijing Demand For Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's power load hit a record
high this morning at 5.36 million kw because of the more than 36-
degree-centigrade weather that has lasted 9 days.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the city's power supply department said that Beijing
has supplied more than 100 million kwh every day for quite a few
days, the largest amount ever in history.
</P>
<P>
People are turning on more air conditioners, some 1.5-million-
kw worth, just to get away from the heat.
</P>
<P>
The city's power supply authorities promise that Beijing's
power supply network, which has been upgraded in the past two
years, ia able to supply sufficient electricity. 
</P>
