<HEADLINE> More Foreign Students Interested in Chinese Language </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A record number of foreign students
graduated from Chinese language programs at the Beijing Languages
and Culture University here today.
</P>
<P>
Of the 200-plus students from 27 countries who received degrees
in the university today, 114 were students of Chinese language, 81
were in business and trade in the Chinese language, 17 studied
Chinese culture, and 18 got degrees in Chinese language and
culture.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, said an official of the university, which
leads other Chinese schools in taking in foreign students, the
number of students from developed countries has been increasing
and their fields of study has also been expanding, along with
China's rapid economic development.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, foreign students were mainly from developing
countries in Asia and Africa, he added.  
