<HEADLINE> Palma Universiada to Take over 400 Doping Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Palma Universiade will
take more than 400 doping tests during the 12-day competitions
which will raise its curtain tomorrow, officials said here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The number of tests is still without counting the ones that
will be performed in case of record beating and tests that are
asked by the corresponding elevation to ratify the record, said
Rodriguez Cano, delegate of the Anti-drugs Taking Commission of
the Superior Council of Sports (CSD).
</P>
<P>
Every morning, the FISU will decide what event and whom will be
tested, bur normally these people would be the first classified in
the different sports, he said, adding that the results of the
tests will be ready after 48 hours.
</P>
<P>
Due to the shortage of specialists, FISU gave a course in
October on sample collection to the 26 doctors that will serve the
duty.
</P>
<P>
Anti-drugs taking checks have been taken in the Universiade
since they are performed in the Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
