<HEADLINE> Nebiolo Believes Beijing Will Hold Best Ever Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA DE MALLORCA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- FISU president Primo
Nebiolo said here on Monday that he believes Beijing will host the
best ever world university games in 2001.
</P>
<P>
After hearing Beijing mayor Liu Qi's report on the works
Beijing had done in preparation of the 2001 university games in
the 20th FISU general assembly, Nebiolo said: "I'm quite sure
Beijing will hold the best ever universiade in 2001, and I'm very
proud for having brought the games to Beijing."
</P>
<P>
"Beijing enjoys an important position not only in international
sports, but also in international politics," said Nebiolo, who is
also IAAF president.
</P>
<P>
He said Beijing has the capacity to build up ideal stadiums and
create benign atmosphere for the 2001 universiade.
</P>
<P>
Liu said in his report that Beijing now boasts over 30 large
stadiums, which can meet the demand of the games.
</P>
<P>
In case of fund shortage, Beijing government will offer their
backing to ensure the games a complete success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
