<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Up Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 2 (Xinhua) --The Composite Stock Index on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange rebounded to above 1,600 points today,
after a sharp drop of about 130 points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Trading hit a record high and finished at about 1,739 points on
this week's first trading session, amidst a bullish mood that was
buoyed up by encouraging words from the authorities. But, it
started falling on Wednesday and dropped to 1,560 points the
following day. About 270 stocks suspended trading because they had
lost more than 10 percent in one day.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese investors have been complaining that the nose-dive
was irrational because they have never thought of such a sudden
fall, according to market observers, but most investors are still
confident in market prospects and the stock market is expected to
continue to grow next week.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai rebounded to 1,613.53 points today, 1.23 percent more
than last Friday. Total trading was 142.6 billion yuan this week,
about 0.66 percent lower than for last week.
</P>
<P>
B shares, which are reserved for overseas investors, also
finished at 55.66 points today, about 0.66 percent lower than for
last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Total B share transactions were estimated at 1.36 billion yuan
this week, and funds trading amounted to 13.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover in bonds was 40 billion yuan for the week, an
increase of 3.4 billion yuan over last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
