<HEADLINE> Late Zimbabwean VP Declared National Hero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Late Zimbabwean Vice-President
Joshua Nkomo, who died of prostate cancer in Harare early Thursday
morning, has been declared a national hero and will be buried with
full military honor at the National Heroes Acre next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Political Bureau of the ruling Zimbabwe African National
Union Patriotic Front met at the Zimbabwe House in Harare
Thursday following the death of the veteran politician and
declared him a national hero, the daily Herald reported Friday .
</P>
<P>
Secretary for Information and Publicity of the ruling party,
Nathan Shamyuarire said that Nkomo's body would be flown to
Bulawayo, the country' s second largest city where it will be
taken to his Matsheumhlope home Friday.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the body will be Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe, among other senior government and ruling party officials.
</P>
<P>
Nkomo's body will Sunday be flown back to Harare and buried
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The government has declared six days of mourning, starting
Thursday until next Tuesday, and all flags must fly at half-mast
during this period. 
</P>
