most prestigious institution of higher learning, gave scholarships
to 35 foreign students today for the first time in its history, a
university spokesman announced.
</P>
<P>
The school's vice-president, Chi Huisheng, said that the
scholarships are designed to encourage foreign students in their
studies and to attract more foreign students who face economic
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the decision-making process for giving them is
entirely open and is held to high standards.
</P>
<P>
The scholarships range from 2,000 yuan (260 U.S. dollars) to 15,
000 yuan and they will be given annually.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of New China in 1949, nearly 20,000 foreign
students have studied at the university and more than 1,000
foreign students are enrolled there now. 
