<HEADLINE> Philippine Cuts Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Central Bank
announced Friday that it will cut the key overnight rates by
another 12.5 basis points each on Monday, the 20th rate cut this
year.
</P>
<P>
The cuts will bring the overnight borrowing rate to 9.0 percent
and overnight lending to 11.0 percent from the previous level of
9.125 percent and 11.125 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
"This move along with the two-percentage point reduction in the
reserve requirements effective July 2 reflects the sustained
efforts of the monetary authorities to bring down the cost of bank
lending while ensuring adequate liquidity in the system," the bank
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Central Bank Governor Gabrial Singson said he expected the twin
measures would encourage banks to resume active lending.
</P>
<P>
The bank has so far cut its key rates by 437.5 basis points
since the start of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
