<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Stock Market Rebounds As Investors' Confidence Regains (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stock traders say that the jittery stock market has calmed down,
with Chinese investors still confident in market prospects. They
say that short-term adjustments are necessary and that this will
help the long-term healthy development of the market.
</P>
<P>
Trading on the Shenzhen market soared to a historic high of 526
points on Tuesday, in a bullish mood buoyed by encouraging words
from authorities in recent weeks. But, on Wednesday, the stock
index began dropping drastically.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts say that the returning confidence is the result
of the Central Government's strategy of pooling funds to reform
state-owned enterprises through the stock market. The Shenzhen
Stock Exchange has raised nearly three billion yuan for several
large state-owned businesses in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Many securities companies have been given approval for
increasing capital by bringing in more shareholders. Some
securities investment funds have also been approved.
</P>
<P>
Financial analysts say that the average prices of stocks are
reasonable in spite of the recent bullish mood.
</P>
</TEXT>
