<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Receive U.N. Grant for Development Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive nearly 440
million taka (9.02 million U.S. dollars) as grant from two United
Nations agencies for a local governance development fund project,
the national news agency BSS reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement in this regard was signed here on Friday between
the Bangladeshi government and the two U.N. agencies.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Capital Development Fund (UNCDF) and the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP) will provide the grant
to Bangladesh to implement the project in Sirajganj district, 113
kilometers northwest of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total grant, the UNCDF will provide 7.3 million
dollars while the UNDP will give the rest.
</P>
<P>
The project, which has been launched on Thursday and will be
completed in 66 months, aims to provide improved and participatory
local governance for socio-economic development and poverty
alleviation in the project area.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the infrastructures including construction of roads
and small culverts under the project area will also be developed
for creating rural employment and poverty alleviation. 
</P>
