<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Materia Medica Book for China's Largest Ethnic Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China has just published a book of
materia medica for the Zhuang ethnic group, the country's largest
ethnic minority.
</P>
<P>
The 16 million people of the ethnic group reside mainly in
southern China in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
For hundreds of years, members of the ethnic group have
developed many types of medicines and diagnostic and curative
theories.
</P>
<P>
To protect these discoveries, the Chinese government got
scientists to prepare an academic compilation of medical history
of the Zhuang covering the past 2,000 years. The book took them 15
years and appears in both the Han and Zhuang languages. The Han
people are the country's ethnic majority. The book contains a
medical history, medical theories, descriptions of 200 medicines,
and treatment procedures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
