<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Establishes New Military Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China established four new military
schools today by a decree of President Jiang Zemin who is also
chairman of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
They are the Shijiazhuang Army Command College, Information
Engineering University, Science and Engineering University and
Institute of Artillery Corps of the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The PLA Shijiazhuang Army Command College was made by combining
the Army General Staff College and the Armored Force Command
College to train middle-ranking officers.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Information Engineering University was made by
combining PLA Institute of Information Engineering, the PLA
Electronic Technology College, and the PLA Survey and Mapping
College. It has a total of 10,000 students and teaching staff and
aims to provide high-quality military professionals in a variety
of fields for modernization of national defense.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Science and Engineering University was made from the
PLA Institute of Communications Engineering, the PLA Engineering
Institute of Engineering Corps, the Meteorology Institute of the
Air Force, and the PLA General Staff Headquarters' No.63 Research
Institute. It will train people for information warfare and for
automating communications, engineering, meteorology, and commands.
It will also serve as an important center for scientific and
technological and military equipment developments for national
defense in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Institute of Artillery Corps was made from the Hefei
Institute of Artillery Corps and Nanjing Institute of Artillery
Corps Institute and will train officers for the artillery corps.
</P>
</TEXT>
