<HEADLINE> Talks Between DPRK, ROK Adjourn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (ROK) suspended their vice-
ministerial talks here today for the profound differences between
the two sides on a number of issues.
</P>
<P>
No substantial results were achieved after three talks in the
past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
The two sides differed on the agenda of separated family
reunion in the talks, as well as the naval skirmish in the
disputed waters on the Yellow Sea and the ROK fertilizer aid to
DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Yang Young-Sik, head of the ROK delegation, said that the
suspension "does not mean the breakup of the talks" for the two
sides still can exchange messages at the truce village of
Panmunjom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
