<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Operates Well This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
witnessed booming business in both passenger and cargo traffic in
the first half of the year, the latest figures released by the
airport show.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, the airport handled more than 1.25
million passengers, an increase of 24 percent over the same period
of last year. In the meantime, cargo transportation rose by 6
percent.
</P>
<P>
At present, 13 airline companies are using the airport,
operating passenger and freight business between Macao and 20
destinations around the world, which include nine cities in the
mainland areas of China and two cities in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the airport in the beginning of the year
indicate that the number of passengers using the airport in 1998
exceeded 2.21 million, which grew by 13.4 percent over that in
1997.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, passengers moving between Macao and Taiwan accounted
for 66.4 percent of the total and those between Macao and the
Chinese mainland accounted for 28.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
