Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- After the French government and central bank failed to
arrange a consensus agreement between the three major private
banks -- the Banque Nationale de Paris (BNP), the Paribas and the
Societe Generale, which were engaged in a merger war, the BNP lost
no time to launch a higher bid to take over the other two banks on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
-- The United States has declassified thousands of pages of
secret documents on rule of Augustus Pinochet in Chile. The
declassified documents were also censored to preserve the identity
of some people and keep secret the "sources."
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The market now has all the cards in its hand after the BNP
launched an overbidding against the Parisbas and Societe Generale
on Thursday, raising the buying price for them from 36 billion
euros (37.44 billion U.S. dollars) to 38 billion euros (39.52
billion U.S. dollars). Unless a foreign bank intervenes, the
merger battle between the three banks, which has been going on for
five months, is not expected to see an exit. 
</P>
