<HEADLINE> Ex-KGB Chief Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Former Chairman of the Soviet Union'
s KGB Viktor Chebrikov died "a sudden death" Friday at the age of
76, according to the Russian Federal Security Service (FSB), the
main successor to the KGB.
</P>
<P>
Chebrikov, who served as the KGB chief in 1982-1988, was born
in the Ukrainian city of Dneproptrovsk on April 27, 1923, and had
been in leading positions in the KGB system since 1967, the Itar-
Tass news agency reported. 
</P>
