<HEADLINE> Australian Shares Continue Strong Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares closed firmer
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 26.8 points, or 0.9 percent,
firmer at 3,028.9 after rises across the industrial and resource
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index firmed 22.9 points to 1,270.3 with gold
stocks again among the better performers while The industrials
index put on 36.9 points to 5,262.8.
</P>
<P>
Positive sentiment surrounding the outlook for U.S. interest
rates fueled gains in most regional shares.
</P>
<P>
The best performed major was media giant News Corp. Its
ordinary shares put on 46.1 cents to 13.507 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Most of the major banks ended in positive territory, pushing
the banking index up 21.5 points to 6,551.3.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth Bank added 25 cents to 24.28 Australian
dollars, National Australia Bank was 3 cents higher at 25.08
Australian dollars, Westpac bank rose 7 cents to 9.9 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Diversified miner BHP ended 14.1 cents up at 18.134 Australian
dollars and Rio Tinto rose 45 cents to 25.8 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume totaled 512.77 million stocks traded worth 908 million
U.S. dollars. Rises outpaced falls 758 to 515 and 402 stocks were
steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
