<HEADLINE> Chinese Woman Soprano Wins French Music Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Jialin, a 28-year-old Chinese
woman soprano, won Thursday night the grand prize of opera
category at the 22nd International Competition of Singing of Paris.
</P>
<P>
A total of 82 candidates of lyrical singing, including 52 women
and 30 men, participated in the competition which began on June 25.
</P>
<P>
Another grand prize of the competition, the grand prize of
interpretation in the category of French melody, was won by two
French singers, baritone Pierre-Yves Pruvot, 28, and baritone
Patrice Verdelet, 35.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jialin was selected by China to join this competition
after she studied singing in Marseille for a period of time.
</P>
<P>
She beat six other finalists with the air singing of "Louise"
of Charpentier's "Depuis le Jour..." and "Butterfly" of Puccini,
with the company of Montpellier Philharmonic Orchestra. 
</P>
