<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed slightly
higher on Singapore Stock Market Friday supported by the gains in
regional markets and on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) closed 7.7 points
higher to end at 2,222.45, a record high for the second
consecutive session.
</P>
<P>
Total volume exceeded 1.676 billion shares valued at 1.881
billion Singapore dollars (about 1.106 billion U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 187 to 150 with 108 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung was the most active stock with a turnover of 56.66
million shares. It was followed by AFP that had 55.04 million
units done. Liang Ht was the next with 54.02 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture continued to lead gainers of the day with a gain of 70
cents to close at 14.1 Singapore dollars. Asean climbed 65 cents
to finish at 10.5 U.S. dollars. DBS rose 60 cents to end at 18.4
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH was the biggest loser of the day with a
loss of 73 cents at 29.9 Singapore dollars. Creative 50, SIA and
SembLog lost 30 cents to finish at 22.5, 14.6 and 6.45 Singapore
dollars respectively. Bukit Sem, 0CBC and 0CBC F each shed 20
cents to finish at 19, 12.7 and 14.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the overnight rally on Wall Street, which saw the
Dow Jones Industrial Average Index close 95.62 points higher,
contributed to Friday's gains. 
</P>
