<HEADLINE> Brazil Edges Nigeria in World Cup Quarterfinal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Brazil blew a 3-0 lead in the
last 30 minutes of regulation but beat Nigeria 4-3 on Sissi's
score in the 14th minute of the first overtime of the Women's
World Cup tournament here tonight.
</P>
<P>
Sissi blasted a powerful curling shot in the 104th minute to
put an end to the grueling fight. It was the first golden goal in
the tournament. Sissi, with two more goals today, is leading all
the shooters with eight goals.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will take on the United States, who beat Germany earlier
today 3-2, in the semifinal on July 4. The other two semifinal
teams are China and defending champions Norway, which will clash
with each other on July 4 in Boston.
</P>
<P>
Brazil looked very sharp in the first half, opening the scoring
in the 5th minute through Sissi, who seized a chance to put a ball
into the net during a goalmouth malee.
</P>
<P>
Brazil made it 2-0 in the 22nd minute when Cidinha received a
Sissi's cross to hit a brilliant header into the right low corner.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's third goal was a 25-meter shot by Nene, who unleashed
the powerful blast from the right and caught Nigeria's goalkeeper
Ann Chejine unprepared. Chiejine was quickly sent out of the field.
</P>
<P>
As most the 54,600 home crowd thought it was a lopsided game,
the Africans all of sudden came into live. They surged back
strongly to level the score in the last 30 minutes of the regular
time.
</P>
<P>
After today's actions, China, the United States, Norway, Brazil,
Germany, Nigeria, Sweden, along with host team Australia have
qualified for the Olympics next year. Russia, which was beaten by
China 0-2 yesterday, lost the chance to go to Sydney. 
</P>
