<HEADLINE> Chinese Athletes Capture Five More Golds in Special Olympics Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RALEIGH, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese athletes captured five gold,
three silver and three bronze medals at the on-going 10th Special
Olympics World Summer Games Thursday in Raleigh, capital of North
Carolina State of the United States.
</P>
<P>
In women's gymnastics, Li Hongxue got one gold and two silver
medals. Yang Yan obtained one gold and one bronze medals, while
Jia Sirui captured one gold and one bronze.
</P>
<P>
In athletics competition, Zhang Jie gained one gold in women's
softball throwing, while Li Xiang captured one gold in men's
softball throwing. Gao Fuxin took bronze in men's 50-meter dash.
</P>
<P>
In aquatics, Jin Juanjuan captured one silver in women's 50-
meter backstroke and one bronze in women's 100-meter breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
Since the game opened on June 26, the Chinese players have
captured nine gold, four silver and six bronze medals in the
competition.
</P>
<P>
Some 7,000 athletes with mental retardation from 152 countries
and regions are competing in 19 events including aquatics,
athletics, badminton, basketball, bocce, bowling, cycling,
equestrian, golf, gymnastics, powerlifting, roller skating,
sailing, soccer, softball, table tennis, team handball, tennis and
volleyball.
</P>
<P>
The nine-day game are being held at venues throughout Raleigh
and its nearby towns of Durham, Chapel Hill and Cary.
</P>
<P>
The 10th Special Olympics World Summer Games, sanctioned by the
Special Olympics International (SOI), is the world's largest
sports event of the year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1968 when it was established, the SOI has staged nine
summer Special Olympics Games and six winter versions.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, composed of 58 mentally disabled people, is
taking part in such disciplines as soccer, basketball, athletics,
swimming, gymnastics and table tennis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
