<HEADLINE> Tree in SW China Recognized as Mother of World's Metasequoia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A 300-year-old rare metasequoia
tree growing in the Huangshui Forest Park in the Shizhu Tujia
Autonomous County, southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, was
recently recognized as the "mother of the world's metasequoia".
</P>
<P>
The tree, which the Ministry of Forestry designated as "China's
No.1 Metasequoia", is over 100 meters tall and has a diameter of 1.
5 meters. The tree's crown covers some 300 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The Huangshui area is home to 28 metasequoia trees which are
widely recognized as "living fossils".
</P>
<P>
Seeds of the oldest metasequoia tree have been supplied to
Japan, the United States, Canada, Germany, Britain and Australia.
The venerable tree is a major scenic site in the forest park.
</P>
</TEXT>
