<HEADLINE> China to Offer More Financial Support to Best Labs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua)-- China is to evaluate its 153 state
key laboratories and select the best 20 and offer more financial
support and help them to update equipment.
</P>
<P>
"The National Natural Science Foundation (NNSF), entrusted by
the Ministry of Science and Technology, will assemble a team of
experts to assess the state laboratories and other open labs under
various government departments in order to improve their
management," said Zhang Cunhao, director of the foundation.
</P>
<P>
Yang Qiwen, vice-director of the basic science research
department of the Ministry of Science and Technology, said the
ministry will increase financial support to the best labs.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, the worst 20 labs in the evaluation will
receive no support from the ministry," Yang said, adding that if
they do not improve in the coming five years, they will lose their
status as state key laboratories.
</P>
<P>
China has invested about 1.4 billion yuan (about 169 million US
dollars) to build 153 state key laboratories since 1984 and they
are evaluated every five years.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said a large amount of major scientific research has been
conducted in them over the past 15 years, and they attracted many
outstanding scientists.
</P>
<P>
"The labs are open to both domestic and overseas scientists,
and several labs have reached the world level in achievement and
efficiency," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
