<HEADLINE> Shandong Opens Wider To Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
been accelerating its opening up and intends to further boost
local economic development by opening even wider to the outside
world.
</P>
<P>
The province now has economic and trade ties with more than 180
countries and regions. Local foreign trade has grown by 15.9
percent annually in the past two decades, with exports rising 13.4
percent per year.
</P>
<P>
Shandong did 16.6 billion US dollars of imports and exports in
1998, accounting for 22.5 percent of local GDP.
</P>
<P>
During the first five months of this year, the province
conducted 6.75 billion US dollars of foreign trade, including 4.22
billion US dollars of exports, a 5.3 percent rise on a yearly
basis, 10.6 percentage points higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has restructured its export mix and focused on the
export of manufactured goods.
</P>
<P>
In the past two decades, Shandong actually used 23.2 billion US
dollars of overseas investment and set up a total of more than 21,
000 overseas-funded enterprises, 10,245 of which have become
operational and handled a combined 26 billion US dollars of
exports.
</P>
<P>
Shandong introduced 3.6 billion US dollars of overseas
investment in 1998, accounting for 14.5 percent of local fixed
assets investment of that year, and half of the overseas money was
spent on technological improvement in local existing enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
