<HEADLINE> Hefei Introduces New Urban Planning Blueprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Hefei, capital of east China's Anhui
Province, has received State Council approval to begin a new round
urban planning, which will last through the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The new blueprint adheres to the sustained development strategy
which centers on improving the use of local scientific research
and education advantages and promoting the development of the high
technology and service sectors.
</P>
<P>
The urban population will be limited to 1.35 million people in
the year 2000 and 1.65 million in 2010.
</P>
<P>
Construction projects in urban areas will be strictly
controlled in a 125 sq.km. in the year 2000 and 150 sq.km. in 2010.
</P>
<P>
Hefei will strengthen efforts to improve the local environment
and transform itself into a garden-like city with advanced
economic, cultural and education systems. 
