<P>
Although the supporters of the National Resistance Movement
hailed the version of the bill passed as fair law which levels the
political playing field while most of the multi-partist MPs stayed
away from the final session of the House.
</P>
<P>
The bill was expected to be assented by President Yoweri
Museveni to beat the deadline.
</P>
<P>
Under the Constitution, any person will from Friday be free to
canvass for public support for a political system of his or her
choice.
</P>
<P>
There was reportedly less tension in the sitting as most of the
 amendments proposed by either Justice Minister Mayanja Nkangi or
Legal Affairs Committee Chairman Wandera Ogallo were quickly
approved.
</P>
<P>
A referendum will be held between June 3 and July 2 in the year
2000 to determine the political system to be used to govern the
country.
</P>
<P>
Multi-partists hold that a general election should be held
first and that all parties should be allowed to participate in the
election, a request flatly turned down by the ruling party.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
