<HEADLINE> Ancient Tombs Unearthed In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists have
completed excavation of two 4,000 year old plus tombs in Fengqiao
Town of Jiaxing City in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Items unearthed from the tombs include pottery, jade, stone
utensils, and human skeletons. The findings are important for the
further study of ancient Chinese civilization.
</P>
<P>
The tombs date back to the Liangzhu Culture, which is one of
the sources of Chinese civilization and was first discovered in
1936 at Liangzhu Town in the province.
</P>
<P>
The Liangzhu Culture featured black painted pottery, jade, and
the world's oldest silk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
