bombers were reportedly intercepted by U.S. fighter jets near
Iceland.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said that the incident was
not "a militarily significant event." However, the Washington
Post said the U.S.-Russian warplane encounter astounded U.S.
officials and underlined recent Western concerns about the
military leadership in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Two Russian strategic bombers flew within striking distance of
the United States last week as part of Moscow's largest military
exercise --West-99 -- since the end of the Cold War, The
Washington Post reported in its Thursday's edition. (US-Russia-
Warplanes)
