demanding the return of the arms and vehicles they took from a
Kenyan army platoon.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the Somali militiamen Tuesday evening
crossed the Kenya-Somalia border and snatched two five-ton
vehicles and several G-3 rifles from 23 Kenyan soldiers who were
on a routine surveillance in Norther Eastern Province of Kenya.
