unpleasant to the militia group, Moi added.
</P>
<P>
Moi made the warning when he was speaking at opening ceremony
of a national show organized by the Agricultural Society of Kenya
at Nakuru, a city in central Kenya, local media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Kenyan government Thursday also issued an
ultimatum to the southern Somali militia group for returning the
stolen ordnance.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Air Force fighter-bombers flew into Somali Thursday with
full armament loads and returned to base full-load, giving a
warning of full- fledge military retaliation if the hardware
robbed from the Kenyan soldiers is not immediately returned.
