<HEADLINE> German FM to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Joschka
Fischer is expected to pay an official visit to Turkey on July 21
to 22, local Daily News reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
On July 21, Fischer will arrive in Istanbul, the largest city
of Turkey, where he is to hold talks with his Turkish counterpart
Ismail Cem later in the day.
</P>
<P>
The talks will cover a broad range of issues, particularly
Turkey's bid for European Union (EU) membership, the fate of
Abdullah Ocalan, leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK), the Kosovo issue, the Cyprus problem and the issues facing
the Turkish community in Germany.
</P>
