<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heavy Rainfall Stops in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- After ten days of heavy downpours
the rain finally stopped along the middle and lower reaches of the
Yangtze river this morning, the Central Meteorology Station (CMS)
has reported.
</P>
<P>
"There are still a few raindrops but it has mostly ended," said
a relieved Li Yanxiang, a research fellow from the CMS.
</P>
<P>
Since June 22, heavy rains have fallen in Zhejiang, Jiangsu,
Anhui and Jiangxi provinces, causing floods along some part of the
Yangtze River. The total rainfall has far exceeded normal average
levels in these areas, noted the CMS.
</P>
<P>
And yesterday the water levels of the Taihu and Hangjiahu lakes
reached a record high.
</P>
<P>
Li blamed the adverse weather conditions on cold and hot air
meeting high in the atmosphere and lingering around these areas
over the past couple of weeks.
</P>
<P>
She predicted that no further heavy rainfall will occur in the
next couple of days in these areas but that showers and thunder
showers may occur after July 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
