<HEADLINE> PLA Information Engineering University Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Information Engineering
University of the People's Liberation Army of China (PLA) was
established today in this capital of central China's Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The university is a combination of the PLA Zhengzhou
Information Engineering College, the PLA Electronic Technology
College and the PLA Topography College.
</P>
<P>
As one of the five comprehensive PLA universities, the
university has a total of 10,000 students and teaching staff. It
has two post-doctoral research centers, eight doctoral research
centers and 22 masters-degree education centers.
</P>
<P>
The university aims to provide high-quality military
professionals in a variety of fields for modernization of national
defense.  
</P>
</TEXT>
