<HEADLINE> Expressway Company Sells Shares on Shenzhen Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A Beijing-based expressway
construction company today sold 1.276 billion yuan (153 million US
dollars) worth of shares on the Shenzhen Securities Exchange at 3.
82 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The North China Expressway Co., Ltd. plans to invest 2.8
billion yuan to build a section of the 658 kilometers long
expressway from Beijing to Shenyang in northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The funds raised today will be used in the construction on the
40-kilometer long Beijing section of the highway, which will open
to traffic in October this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China will meet its highway construction
peak this year, recording a total investment of over 500 billion
yuan in the field.  
</P>
</TEXT>
