<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Rice Exports Drop Due to Low Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The demand for the rice on the world market had dropped
sharply, and the strength of the baht had also meant that
importers had delayed placing orders, the newspaper quoted Thai
Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce Minister Supachai Panichpakdi
as saying.
</P>
<P>
In baht terms, Thailand's rice exports in the first half of
this year were worth 31.22 billion baht compared with 45.55
billion baht in the same period last years -- a fall of 31
percent.
</P>
<P>
The export volume fell to 2.83 million tones from 3.31 million
tones in the same period last year, a drop of 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the export level is expected to rise in the second
half of the year because Thai exporters are expected to offer more
attractive prices, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is the biggest exporter of rice in the world with the
export volume amounted to 6.5 million tones last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
