<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's GDP Growth Rate Declines in the First Half of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's gross domestic product
(GDP) in the first six months of this year grew 4.3 percent,
according to Vietnam's General Department of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate dropped nearly two percentage points compared
with the 6.16 percent GDP growth rate for the first half of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate in industrial and construction sector in the
first half of the year was 7.4 percent, down from 9.98 percent in
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned industrial sector performed poorly with the 3.6
percent growth rate compared with 10.2, 10.7 and 13.4 percent in
the first half of 1998, 1997 and 1996 respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, the growth rate in agricultural, forestry and
aquaculture was 2.7 percent, up from 2.12 percent during the
corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has harvested 14 million tones of rice, 1.4 million
tones of winter-spring cereal crops this year. The total
winter-spring grain yield reached 15.4 million tones, 500,000
tones more than that of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The service sector also saw a low growth rate due to poor
performance of trade. The total output value from the retail sales
and services were estimated at 90,000 billion Vietnamese dong
(6.47 billions U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
