<DOCNO> XIE19990702.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Archers Optimistic of Qualifying for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Indonesian Archery
Association (Perpani) Hayono Isman was optimistic that his women
archers would qualify for the 2000 Olympics in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Hayono said the four archers -- Nurfitriyana Saiman Lantang,
Hamdiah Lusia Elizabeth and Kusumawardhani -- improved their
scores during training for the World Championships in Riom, France,
from July 22 to July 26.
</P>
<P>
"They will fly to Seoul on July 12 for a warm-up before going
to Riom," the former state minister of youth affairs and sports
was quoted by The Jakarta Post Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The squad will be accompanied by South Korean coach Lee Jae-
hyun and Donald Pandiangan.
</P>
<P>
Perpani secretary-general Udi Harsono said Indonesian archers
would have to reach the championships' quarterfinals to qualify
for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian archers would need to attain at least 3,845 points
to reach the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
"Up to today, their total scores have reached above 3,880. I
believe if they can perform consistently, they will qualify for
the Olympics," he said.
</P>
<P>
If the archers do not qualify from their ranking at the
championships, they will have a second chance in the Asian
Championships in Beijing from September 1 to 5.
</P>
<P>
Hayono said that Perpani faced financial difficulties in
providing about 2 billion rupiah (296,750 U.S. dollars) for
preparation of the archers from February to the Olympics in
September next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
