<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchanges on
Thursday closed slightly up with the benchmark IPC index surging
by 25.09 points, or 0.43 percent, at 5,854.60 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 140.052 million shares for some 264.038
million U.S. dollars against 96.019 million shares worth 177.433
million dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.50 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.55 for sale and 9.25 for purchase on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Since Wednesday, the Mexican stocks have maintained higher
following the U.S. Federal Reserve's decision to increase its
interest rate to 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said higher U.S. interest rates tend to push Mexican
rates higher and pull capital flows out of riskier emerging market
securities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
