<HEADLINE> Sweden's Kammerling Breaks Women's 50m Butterfly World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Anna-Karin Kammerling
clocked 26.39 seconds to break the women's 50 meters butterfly
world record at the Swedish swimming championships in Halmstad on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
She shaved 0.15 seconds off the previous mark set by Inge De
Bruin of the Netherlands one week ago.
</P>
<P>
Kammerling said she reduced the training load some time before
the championships and that gave her the best form for the record-
breaking swim. 
</P>
