<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNHCR Leader Attacks NATO Countries for Being </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. High Commissioner
for Refugees(UNHCR) Thursday sharply criticized NATO governments
for having spent billions of U.S. dollars to bomb Yugoslavia in
the name of returning ethnic Albanians to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Of the 400 million U.S. dollars the U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) has said it needs to help the more than 850,000
refugees return from camps and rebuild their homes and lives in
Kosovo, only 140 million U.S. dollars has been received, said
Soren Jessen-Petersen, the deputy high commissioner of the U.N.
refugee agency.
</P>
<P>
"I find it unacceptable that the international community is not
in the position to give us the necessary funds," he told a news
conference here.
</P>
<P>
He said he had strongly appealed for more money to the foreign
ministers and officials from 18 countries who gathered at U.N.
headquarters on Wednesday to discuss the U.N. effort in Kosovo,
including caring for the refugees who fled the province.
</P>
<P>
Thursday morning, the number of ethnic Albanians who had returned
to Kosovo since the end of NATO's 11-week air campaign reached the
half-million mark, the deputy UNHCR chief said.
</P>
<P>
The priority needs are now for emergency shelter materials,
such as tents, blankets, mattresses, plywood, window frames, nails
and tools so the refugees can begin repairing at least part of
their homes so they have proper shelter before winter begins, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
